# orcasecurity_integration_jira_cloud_template (Resource)

Manages a [Jira Cloud](https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira) template in Orca
Security. The template defines which Atlassian Cloud project / issue type Orca
opens issues in, how alert fields map to Jira fields, and how Jira workflow
transitions reflect back as Orca alert state changes.

Credentials for Jira Cloud are stored on a separate Orca resource (OAuth via
the Atlassian app). Create the credentials side in the Orca UI, copy its UUID,
and pass it in via the `resource_id` argument.

Under the hood this creates an entry under `POST /api/external_service/config`
with `service_name = "jira"`. Updates go to
`PUT /api/external_service/config/jira?template=<template_name>`.

